						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Pedestal of a broken image in the temple of Vīrabhadra.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription, bearing no date, describes in verse the deity <hi rend="bold">s11antinātha</hi> and the saints <hi rend="bold">Sōmadēvakumāra</hi> and <hi rend="bold">Sudhākaradēva</hi> belonging to <hi rend="bold">Mūla-saṁgha.</hi> It also states that a <hi rend="italic">basadi</hi> was constructed by <hi rend="bold">Sātōja-Rmsōja.</hi> The characters belong to the <hi rend="bold">12th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
